Post Description:
üëâüèº For the list of essential services. 
While F&B outlets remain open, they are only available for delivery and takeaway.
Comments: Its very easy for people to speak with the benefit of hindsight. But a lot of people dont seem to understand that the government functions in a different way compared to individuals. In fact every government needs to look at the bigger picture rather than the small nitty gritty needs of every single person in the country. Any society that functions on the latter will simply see a collapse in the running of daily life. A lot of demands and questions are being raised but a lot of it can and should be dismissed because context is not being taken into account. A lot of ‚ÄòWHY NOW ISNT IT TOO LATE‚Äô can be answered with one word - context. This pandemic is inherently volatile - nothing can be predicted. And thats why in the initial stages it is close to impossible to not do anything about it or completely go into a full panic mode. Why measures were implemented progressively prior to this circuit breaker is to ease people into this transition while keeping the situation relatively under control. If drastic measures are imposed, we will end up like countries such as Italy or India, where the entire country will be thrown into a frenzy and its impacts will simply be expanded and prolonged. Look, even a slight step up in measures imposed can trigger huge waves of panic buying, what gives the government confidence to announce complete shutdowns in the early stages (considering also that there wasnt such a necessity)? There is a natural tendency to oversimplify things in the comments section so for once, just sit down and THINK.
